{
  "id": "js-101",
  "name": "JavaScript Introduction",
  "description": "Introduction to JavaScript in Venus Notebooks — modern JS syntax, arrays, objects, and async patterns",
  "cells": [
    {
      "id": "js-intro-md-1",
      "type": "MARKDOWN",
      "source": "# JavaScript in Venus Notebooks\n\nVenus supports **JavaScript** (Node.js) alongside JShell and Java.\n\n- Click the mode button on any code cell to cycle: **JShell → Java → JS**\n- JavaScript cells run via Node.js — each cell is independent\n- Use `require('package')` to import npm packages\n- Built-in `venus` helpers: `venus.table()`, `venus.display()`, `venus.stats()`\n\n> **Install npm packages** in the Packages tab → npm section.",
      "output": "",
      "executed": false
    },
    {
      "id": "js-intro-1",
      "type": "CODE",
      "mode": "nodejs",
      "source": "//@ anchor: hello-world-in-java-script\n//@ description: Hello World in JavaScript\n// Hello World in JavaScript\nconsole.log('Hello from Venus Notebooks!');\nconsole.log('Node.js version:', process.version);\nconsole.log('Platform:', process.platform);",
      "output": "",
      "executed": false,
      "anchor": "hello-world-in-java-script",
      "description": "Hello World in JavaScript"
    },
    {
      "id": "js-intro-md-2",
      "type": "MARKDOWN",
      "source": "## Modern JavaScript Syntax\n\nVenus runs Node.js, so all ES2022+ features are available.",
      "output": "",
      "executed": false
    },
    {
      "id": "js-intro-2",
      "type": "CODE",
      "mode": "nodejs",
      "source": "//@ anchor: arrow-functions-destructuring-spread\n//@ description: Arrow functions, destructuring, spread\n// Arrow functions, destructuring, spread\nconst numbers = [3, 1, 4, 1, 5, 9, 2, 6, 5, 3];\n\n// Array methods\nconst unique  = [...new Set(numbers)].sort((a,b) => a-b);\nconst evens   = numbers.filter(n => n % 2 === 0);\nconst doubled = numbers.map(n => n * 2);\nconst sum     = numbers.reduce((acc, n) => acc + n, 0);\n\nconsole.log('Original:', numbers.join(', '));\nconsole.log('Unique sorted:', unique.join(', '));\nconsole.log('Evens:', evens.join(', '));\nconsole.log('Doubled:', doubled.join(', '));\nconsole.log('Sum:', sum, '  Average:', (sum / numbers.length).toFixed(2));",
      "output": "",
      "executed": false,
      "anchor": "arrow-functions-destructuring-spread",
      "description": "Arrow functions, destructuring, spread"
    },
    {
      "id": "js-intro-3",
      "type": "CODE",
      "mode": "nodejs",
      "source": "//@ anchor: objects-classes-and-destructuring\n//@ description: Objects, classes, and destructuring\n// Objects, classes, and destructuring\nclass Person {\n  constructor(name, age, role) {\n    this.name = name;\n    this.age  = age;\n    this.role = role;\n  }\n  toString() { return `${this.name} (${this.age}) — ${this.role}`; }\n}\n\nconst team = [\n  new Person('Alice',  30, 'Engineer'),\n  new Person('Bob',    25, 'Designer'),\n  new Person('Carol',  35, 'Manager'),\n  new Person('Dave',   28, 'Engineer'),\n];\n\n// Display as table using Venus helper\nvenus.table(team.map(p => ({ Name: p.name, Age: p.age, Role: p.role })));\n\n// Destructuring\nconst { name, age } = team[0];\nconsole.log(`\\nFirst team member: ${name}, age ${age}`);",
      "output": "",
      "executed": false,
      "anchor": "objects-classes-and-destructuring",
      "description": "Objects, classes, and destructuring"
    },
    {
      "id": "js-intro-md-3",
      "type": "MARKDOWN",
      "source": "## Working with Data\n\nJSON manipulation and functional programming patterns.",
      "output": "",
      "executed": false
    },
    {
      "id": "js-intro-4",
      "type": "CODE",
      "mode": "nodejs",
      "source": "//@ anchor: functional-data-processing\n//@ description: Functional data processing\n// Functional data processing\nconst sales = [\n  { month: 'Jan', region: 'North', amount: 12400 },\n  { month: 'Jan', region: 'South', amount:  8900 },\n  { month: 'Feb', region: 'North', amount: 15600 },\n  { month: 'Feb', region: 'South', amount: 11200 },\n  { month: 'Mar', region: 'North', amount: 13800 },\n  { month: 'Mar', region: 'South', amount: 14300 },\n];\n\n// Group by region\nconst byRegion = sales.reduce((acc, row) => {\n  (acc[row.region] = acc[row.region] || []).push(row.amount);\n  return acc;\n}, {});\n\nconsole.log('Sales by region:');\nObject.entries(byRegion).forEach(([region, amounts]) => {\n  const total = amounts.reduce((s,a) => s+a, 0);\n  const avg   = (total / amounts.length).toFixed(0);\n  console.log(`  ${region}: total=${total.toLocaleString()}  avg=${avg}`);\n});\n\nconsole.log('\\nFull dataset:');\nvenus.table(sales);",
      "output": "",
      "executed": false,
      "anchor": "functional-data-processing",
      "description": "Functional data processing"
    },
    {
      "id": "js-intro-5",
      "type": "CODE",
      "mode": "nodejs",
      "source": "//@ anchor: async-await-with-promises\n//@ description: Async/await with Promises\n// Async/await with Promises\nasync function delay(ms) {\n  return new Promise(resolve => setTimeout(resolve, ms));\n}\n\nasync function fetchSimulated(id) {\n  await delay(10); // simulate network\n  return { id, data: `Record ${id}`, timestamp: new Date().toISOString() };\n}\n\nasync function main() {\n  console.log('Fetching records in parallel...');\n  const results = await Promise.all([1, 2, 3, 4, 5].map(id => fetchSimulated(id)));\n  venus.table(results.map(r => ({ ID: r.id, Data: r.data })));\n  console.log('All done!');\n}\n\nmain();",
      "output": "",
      "executed": false,
      "anchor": "async-await-with-promises",
      "description": "Async/await with Promises"
    },
    {
      "id": "js-intro-6",
      "type": "CODE",
      "mode": "nodejs",
      "source": "//@ anchor: template-literals-optional-chaining-nu\n//@ description: Template literals, optional chaining, nullish coalescing\n// Template literals, optional chaining, nullish coalescing\nconst config = {\n  server: { host: 'localhost', port: 8585 },\n  db: null,\n};\n\nconst host    = config.server?.host ?? 'unknown';\nconst dbHost  = config.db?.host     ?? 'not configured';\nconst timeout = config.server?.timeout ?? 30;\n\nconsole.log(`Server: ${host}:${config.server.port}`);\nconsole.log(`Database host: ${dbHost}`);\nconsole.log(`Timeout: ${timeout}s`);\n\n// Tagged template literal\nfunction highlight(strings, ...values) {\n  return strings.reduce((acc, str, i) => acc + str + (values[i] !== undefined ? `[${values[i]}]` : ''), '');\n}\nconsole.log(highlight`Venus runs on port ${8585} using Node ${process.version}`);",
      "output": "",
      "executed": false,
      "anchor": "template-literals-optional-chaining-nu",
      "description": "Template literals, optional chaining, nullish coalescing"
    },
    {
      "id": "js-intro-md-4",
      "type": "MARKDOWN",
      "source": "## Venus Built-in Helpers\n\nEvery JS cell has access to a `venus` object with display utilities:\n\n| Helper | Description |\n|--------|-------------|\n| `venus.table(arrayOfObjects)` | Print a formatted text table |\n| `venus.display(anything)` | Pretty-print JSON |\n| `venus.stats(numberArray)` | count, min, max, mean, std dev |",
      "output": "",
      "executed": false
    },
    {
      "id": "js-intro-7",
      "type": "CODE",
      "mode": "nodejs",
      "source": "//@ anchor: venus-built-in-helpers-demo\n//@ description: Venus built-in helpers demo\n// Venus built-in helpers demo\nconst data = [\n  { name: 'mercury', distanceAU: 0.39, moons: 0 },\n  { name: 'venus',   distanceAU: 0.72, moons: 0 },\n  { name: 'earth',   distanceAU: 1.00, moons: 1 },\n  { name: 'mars',    distanceAU: 1.52, moons: 2 },\n  { name: 'jupiter', distanceAU: 5.20, moons: 95 },\n];\n\nvenus.table(data);\n\nconsole.log('\\nDistance stats (AU):');\nvenus.stats(data.map(p => p.distanceAU));\n\nconsole.log('\\nJSON display:');\nvenus.display({ planet: 'Venus', symbol: '♀', type: 'Terrestrial' });",
      "output": "",
      "executed": false,
      "anchor": "venus-built-in-helpers-demo",
      "description": "Venus built-in helpers demo"
    }
  ],
